<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2315: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-19T23:00:00+01:00">May 19, 1934—11
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 19—7:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>84. Council this afternoon adopted a report embodying the communication
                            from Mello Franco cited in Wilson’s 256, May 19, 11 a.m. and directed
                            the transmission of a congratulatory telegram to Mello Franco.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
